==English==
===Etymology===
{{D.}} ''fijn'' meaning fine and ''bosch'' meaning bush through Afrikaans. 
===Noun===
# {{Botany}}: Vegetation unique to the Cape Floral Kingdom made up chiefly of [[proteaceae]], [[restio]]s and [[Ericaceae]].
#*'''1992''' Reader's Digest''The Great South African Outdoors'' - The southern and western Cape is the home of a unique type of vegitation known as '''fynbos'''. Covering around 90 000 square kilometers of often harsh terrain, '''fynbos''' is made up of approximately 6 000 different plant species.
